==English==

===Pronunciation===
*lĭft, /lɪft/, /<tt>lIft</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɪft|Rhymes: -ɪft]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# {{UK}} Mechanical device for vertically transporting goods or people between floors in a building: [[elevator]].
#:''Take the '''lift''' to the fourth floor.''
# The act of transporting someone in a vehicle: [[ride]].
#:''He gave me a '''lift''' to the bus station.''
# An upward [[force]], such as the force that keeps aircraft aloft.

====Synonyms====
